README – CSC and Kou indices
This folder contains the Python code and input data used to compute the Clyne-Davies crack susceptibility coefficient (CSC), the Kou cracking susceptibility index (Kou CSI), and the associated liquidus temperature (TL), solidus temperature (TS), and freezing range \Delta Tfor the W-Ti-V, W-Ti-Zr, and W-V-Zr ternary systems.
Files
	CSC_Kou.ipynb – Python code used for the calculations 
	WTiV/ – folder containing Thermo-Calc/Scheil CSV outputs for W-Ti-V 
	WTiZr/ – folder containing Thermo-Calc/Scheil CSV outputs for W-Ti-Zr 
	WVZr/ – folder containing Thermo-Calc/Scheil CSV outputs for W-V-Zr 
	CSC_all_systems.xlsx – output file generated by the code 
What the code does
For each Thermo-Calc/Scheil CSV file, the code:
	reads the liquid fraction, cumulative heat, and temperature data, 
	computes cumulative heat at f_L=0.60, 0.10, and 0.01, 
	computes the Clyne-Davies CSC: 
CSC=\frac{t_v}{t_R}\bigmwith
t_R=(\Delta Q_{0.10-0.60})^2,t_v=(\Delta Q_{0.01-0.60})^2-(\Delta Q_{0.10-0.60})^2
	computes the Kou cracking susceptibility index from the terminal solidification path, 
	extracts: 
	TL [K] as the temperature at maximum liquid fraction, 
	TS [K] as the temperature at minimum liquid fraction, 
	\Delta T=TL-TS
Output
The output workbook CSC_all_systems.xlsx contains one sheet for each ternary system: WTiV, WTiZr, and WVZr.
Notes
	The same workflow was used for all three ternary systems.
	Composition id are sequential and follow compositions given in Solidification/spreading index file (useful information for plotting). 
